<br>
Classes I have been playing or hunted/dueled with:<br>
<br>
Reavers:<br>
--------<br>
<br>
Interesting class and decent tank from what I have seen thusfar. Not sure how they scale at 50 compared to other tanks. I consider the Midgard Beserker to be the deadliest tank in the game. And from what I have seen at 35... the Reaver is holding up nicely. Still haven't seen one beat a Zerker in frenzy, but they give a non-frenzy zerker one heckuva fight. <br>
<br>
Bonedancer:<br>
----------<br>
<br>
While the ablity to have multiple pets is neat, this class really brings nothing new to the table IMO that other pet classes offer. For Midgard in general the Bone Army spec BD brings another class that can AE DoT. Of course that AE DOT isnt as powerful as a Cab or Mentalist, but AE DoT is something that Midgard really hasn't had other than the Shaman.<br>
<br>
Savage:<br>
--------<br>
<br>
Solid tank class from what I have seen, but Zerker is still Midgard's deadliest tank. One interesting twist on the Savage is the 2H Savage instead of the Hand to Hand. Since Savages have a Savagery skill which hastes them... many are opting to use the Haste with a 2hander. Allowing them to hit with 2h damage at 1h speed. <br>
<br>
But Im wondering if this is a class similar to assassins and friars that they really dont come into their prime till 40+. I'm very interested to see how these do as more hit lvl 50. <br>
<br>
Animist:<br>
-------<br>
Very interesting class. Not sure how they will do in RvR yet.  Its a chaotic class that still needs a lot of tweaking, but I think will be a successful class in the right hands. I think its a class that requires players to think out of the box a bit. Many that try to approach it as your typical pet class seem to get frustrated or only find limited uses for them. This class sorta has the feel of an Engineer in Team Fortress to me.<br>
<br>
The Animist is the class I'm currently putting thru the paces. The next class I want to try is a the Reaver so Akasa keep that old Reaver gear you out-grow &lt;winks&gt;.<br>
<br>
