<br>
This was done because necros were putting their pets inside keeps and nuking the hell out of people who couldn't get to the pets.  This LOS exploit was fixed w/n 2 weeks of release (even though enchanters had been using it for a year and mythic ignored the complaints over that).<br>
<br>
Mythic did a 2 part fix.  (1) The necro had to have LOS w/ the target AND his pet.  This affected necros only.  A huge cry was heard from the player base (THANKS FOR FIXING NECROS AND NOT FIXING ENCHANTERS).  So Mythic made part (2) of the patch: Pets must have LOS of their target.  This effected all classes.<br>
<br>
Part (2) of this was workable for all other classes except Necros because Necros still have to do part (1).   Testing on Pendragon shows that it's not hard for one of the 3 LOS to be broken on a hilly field.  Dungeons are a nightmare.  And to make matters worse, You lose the mana when you cast the spell and THEN it checks if you have LOS.  So you're peeing your mana down the drain.<br>
<br>
They should change it so that part (1) of this nerf goes away and only part (2) applies to everyone.  Then it could be &quot;balanced&quot;.<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
<br>
This is one of the reasons I stopped playing last time.  Only it was crafting they changed then.<br>
